  "instructions": [
    "Combine pork back ribs, sugar, palm sugar, and water in a saucepan and bring to a boil over high heat.",
    "Reduce heat to low and simmer for 30 minutes, or until the meat is tender.",
    "Strain the cooking liquid through a fine-mesh sieve into a clean saucepan and discard the solids.",
    "Add coconut milk, agar agar, fish sauce, lime juice, coriander, galangal, salt, and black pepper to the saucepan and whisk until the agar agar is dissolved.",
    "Bring the mixture to a boil over high heat, then reduce the heat to low and simmer for 10 minutes, or until the mixture has thickened.",
    "Remove the saucepan from the heat and let it cool slightly.",
    "Use a spherification agent to create small balls of the mixture.",
    "Serve the khanom thai hot, garnished with chopped peanuts and fresh cilantro.",
    "Refrigerate any leftover khanom thai for up to 24 hours before serving."
  ],
